  "number": 6474,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6474",
  "title": "fix(core): remove searchMetadata",
  "body": "This is redundant with `search.status === 'stalled'`, so all relevant places have been removed:\r\n\r\n- rendering no longer sets searchMetadata\r\n- not used in connectSearchBox\r\n- Widgets use `instance.status === 'stalled'` instead\r\n\r\nNote that for now `isSearchStalled` is still exposed from connectSearchBox as in SearchBox.vue `this.state.instantSearchInstance.status === 'stalled'` breaks an unrelated test, likely related to the timing difference between reading a state and the class. Not ideal but I couldn't find a workaround. Maybe this won't be needed anymore once we have common components?\r\n\r\n[FX-3196]\r\n\r\nBREAKING CHANGE: `searchMetadata` is not exposed on rendering widgets, use `instance.status === 'stalled'` instead.\r\n\r\n\r\n[FX-3196]: https://algolia.atlassian.net/browse/FX-3196?atlOrigin=eyJpIjoiNWRkNTljNzYxNjVmNDY3MDlhMDU5Y2ZhYzA5YTRkZjUiLCJwIjoiZ2l0aHViLWNvbS1KU1cifQ",
